description:
        Hydro Extrusions is a world-leading aluminium extrusion business counting around 100 production sites in 40 countries and employing 20,000 people. Through our unique combination of local expertise, global network, and unmatched R&amp;D capabilities, we can offer everything from standard profiles, to advanced development and manufacturing for most industries.

Since 1905, Hydro has turned natural resources into valuable products for people and businesses with focus on a safe and good workplace for our 30,000 employees in more than 140 locations.

Hydro is committed to leading the way in shaping a sustainable future and in doing so, creating more viable societies by developing natural resources into products and solutions in innovative and efficient ways to industries that matter.


Job Location: 
 Mississauga


Hydro employees can enjoy several benefits including:



Medical, Rx, Dental, Disability, Life Insurance, Flexible Spending Accounts

Retirement Savings Plans with Company Match/Contributions

Education Assistance

Bonus Plan Eligibility

Parental Leave




Job Summary: 
In this key role, the HR Manager Mississauga is a strategic business partner and is a member of the Location Lead Team; performing Human Resources related duties and carries out responsibilities in all aspects of the Human Resources process.


Required Education/Experience
:


Bachelor’s degree in Business related field or equivalent experience

Proven experience with successful leadership administering HR related programs

Developing processes that foster Employee Engagement 

Familiarity with HRIS and Payroll Systems (i.e. SuccessFactors and UKG)




Preferred Skills/Qualifications
:


Excellent listening/communication abilities to lead improvement processes within various areas and levels of the organization

Proficient in PowerPoint, Microsoft Office, and the ability to learn other software/operating platforms needed 

Skills in conflict resolution is required 




Job Responsibilities:



Work with GBS (Global Business Services) Recruitment to recruit and staff for the facility. Administer the internal bidding process for salaried and hourly positions; recruit externally as needed;

Implement Extrusion North America HR initiatives at the facility, communicate and follow up as needed;

Manage or oversee dispute resolution process with involved parties. Investigate concerns and complaints and work towards a resolution;

Lead all Labour Relations activities – grievance meetings, labour management, contract negotiations, arbitration, build rapport with Union Committee; 

Conduct / Facilitate required training for all staff levels (i.e. Managers, Supervisors, Hourly). Ensure any e-learnings assigned to staff are completed in timely manner; 

Determine effective strategies for addressing future needs in the marketplace; 

Drive the Performance Management and Succession Planning Process. Manage the year-end performance evaluation calibration process to determine high potentials; 

Ensure compliance with labour employment laws, regulations, WSIB, and company values, and the Hydro policies and procedures. Strong working knowledge of the facility’s Collective Bargaining Agreement; 

Oversee all aspects of salaried and hourly payroll and job evaluation process; 

Serve as driving force and an enabler to provide proactive change management practices and help drive the Employee and Safety Culture at the facility; 

Develop and support people systems to promote the lean manufacturing culture; 

Maximize individual and organizational impact through effective organizational development practices; 

Plan, organize Company employee events, communication meetings and be present / available on off-shifts to facilitate these events; 

Proactively provide consultation to management regarding changes that effect employee relations; 

Complete all HR reporting as required and any ad-hoc requests; 

Lead the mentoring program with support from Plant Manager, Health &amp; Safety and Dept Managers; 

Provide support with WSIB claims as needed;

Lead location-wide employee recognition system; 

Develop and lead community relations strategy; 

Technical expertise in Human Resources; 

Other duties as assigned. 




Care, Courage, &amp; Collaboration


At Hydro We care about our People!

We care about Safety!

At Hydro you’re part of a bigger story. A story shaped by you.


