PEL123

Description



Reporting to the accounting operations department’s Senior Manager, Accounts Payable and Revenue, the accounts payable supervisor will supervise unionized employees, identify issues that need addressing and oversee the review of system processes and procedures. The incumbent will prioritize operational tasks in their sector and solve complex, unusual problems. They will provide support to the senior manager and analysts in this sector, as well as to users in other departments. They will produce reports and dashboards, and monitor and measure the results of improvements. They will ensure action plans are executed to prioritize activities to support the organization’s objectives. They also manage their employees’ performance by ensuring quality control and providing appropriate training as needed.



Responsibilities



Management of human resources and operational tasks:


 Supervises employees and operational tasks in the unit;

 Sets priorities and ensures the timely completion of tasks. Measures results and performs follow ups;

 Provides support to the senior manager, accounting operations, and the development analyst (development-related activities);

 Is responsible for implementing and integrating various improvement initiatives within the team;

 Is responsible for coordinating auditors’ internal and external audit work;

 Is responsible for communicating with vendors and internal colleagues to settle disputes;

 Acts as a resource person by offering support to users in their department.




Quality Assurance And Communication




 Performs quality control, develops and validates the report used and follows up with the senior manager, accounts payable;

 Produces and analyzes the unit’s management and statistical reports;

 Reviews and approves the duties of unionized employees in accordance with established standards;

 Provides training and coaching to unionized staff and managers. Manages performance issues;

 Supports the accounting operations support analyst.


Review of processes / procedures / training plans and documentation:


 Manages and documents process reviews and accounts payable system procedures;

 Ensures the implementation of solutions in response to complex and unusual operational problems and communicates the changes to all department clerks and users;

 Is responsible for developing and approving training plans and documentation;

 Participates in tests related to various improvement projects and initiatives;

 Acts as a resource person for the systems in their sector.




Various Reports And Dashboards




 Develops and implements the content of various reports and dashboards;

 Performs analyses based on reports and dashboards;

 Develops action plans for necessary changes.




Requirements




 DEC (college diploma) and 10 years of experience, or bachelor’s degree and 7 years of experience in accounting or business administration;

 7 years of experience in personnel and task management, prioritization and process review for accounting operations processes within an accounts payable department;

 5 years of experience in a role that supports employee development and/or resources. An equivalent combination of education and experience will also be considered;

 Solid knowledge of general accounting and year end accounting processes;

 Knowledge of the Canada Labour Code a valuable asset;

 Extensive knowledge of Microsoft Office (Word/Excel/PowerPoint) and aptitude for systems related to accounting operations. Knowledge of Oracle an asset.




Competencies




 Strong interpersonal skills, highly developed analytical sense and ability to play a key role in change management;

 Ability to work in a changing environment. Flexibility and strong, proven skills in process improvement;

 Excellent oral and written communication skills in both official languages;

 Ability to work under pressure with strict deadlines;

 Development support skills in a unionized environment; demonstrated coaching skills;

 Strong sense of organization and demonstrated ability to manage and prioritize operational tasks.




The Advantages Of Working For VIA Rail




 A fast-paced environment at a company undergoing major transformation;

 A modern work life balance;

 An innovative remote work policy;

 A generous and comprehensive compensation package;

 Bonuses based on individual and corporate performance;

 Attractive benefits (defined contribution pension plan, flexible group insurance plan);

 A railway travel pass you can use to explore the country with friends and family;

 A people first work environment—employment equity, diversity and inclusion are fundamental to our vision of connecting people and places from coast to coast;

 Real commitment and action to support the environment and Canadian communities;

 A workplace who fosters health and well-being for all our employees;

 A wide range of health and wellness benefits for you and your family, including an unlimited access to a telemedicine service.




Condition Of Employment




 VIA Rail is committed to protecting the health and providing a safe environment for its employees and customers. Therefore, in accordance with current policy, VIA Rail requires that all members of its staff be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 and provide proof as a condition of employment.

Job Title: 
 Senior Manager, CommunityPrograms


Status:
 Regular, Full Time


Date Posted:
 March 8, 2022


Closing Date:
 Open until filled


Anticipated Start Date: 
ASAP



The Opportunity



DIVERSEcity Community Resources Society is seeking a 
Manager, Community Programs
 to join our Community Development Department.

Reporting to the Senior Manager, Community Development, the Manager is responsible for the effective and efficient delivery of DIVERSEcity’s Community Programs, including but not limited to Food Justice, Food Security, Canadian Learning Bond and other community focused non-IRCC funded initiatives. This position plays a crucial role in the organization: delivering high-quality programming, building relationships with residents and community partners, and ensuring program improvement through data-driven evaluation The Manager is expected to manage the human resources, financial resources, contracts, and risk within Community Programs, as well as to grow the portfolio through monitoring emerging client and community needs, securing funding for existing and new programs/services and develop responsive and innovative programming that centers around JEDI (justice, equity, inclusion and diversity) principles. The manager will also contribute to the agency’s strategic platform.



Key Responsibilities




 Leads and supports Community Programs programs efficiently and effectively in accordance with best practice, contractual obligations and DIVERSEcity policy and procedures;

 Monitors and ensures program service quality, innovation, participation, utilization and evaluation;

 Ensures program staff are managed from a strength based approach and compliance with Collective Agreement and agency Policies and Procedures

 Prepares budget forecasts of assigned programs and monitors program expenditures, together with the finance department;

 Prepares funding applications and proposals for contract renewals;

 Provides reports to funders, assigned supervisor or Board of Directors, as required;

 Provide supervision and coaching to ensure all staff provide professional, client-centered support which enables culturally agile and excellent service;

 Coaches and supports staff to continuously grow and thrive

 Ensures seamless program delivery by ensuring adequate staffing levels by conducting recruitment, selection and hiring of new personnel;

 Utilizes an intersectional lens to develop services that are tailored appropriately according to age (e.g. youth, adult), culture, socio-economic background, gender, sexual orientation, income, language level, pre and post migration experiences etc to ensure accessibility to all newcomers.

 Participates collaboratively within internal teams, external committees, advisory groups and relevant networks to be informed and updated on emerging issues, build capacity of programming and to advocate on behalf of newcomers to help address service gaps in the community;

 Actively participates in opportunities (both internal and external) for both knowledge and skill development in volunteer and civic engagement program growth and development (e.g. professional development training, coaching, program manager meetings, networking, needs assessment, community growth trends and initiatives);

 Develops annual and long-range program plans to grow the community programs services portfolio;

 Actively develops strategic partnerships with non-traditional sectors and partners;

 Oversees the ongoing engagement and leadership of Food justice/security within Surrey and North Delta

 Conducts contract negotiations under the direction of the Senior Manager and Director, Community Development




Qualified Candidates Will Posses




 University degree in social sciences or relevant;

 Proven recent program development experience, with knowledge of federal, provincial and other funding sources;

 A minimum of 3-years’ experience working in a community based non-profit society or related experience;

 A minimum of 2-years’ experience in program management

 Experience in proposal/grant writing;

 A minimum of 2-years’ experience working with volunteer, civic engagement and/or social integration programming;

 A minimum of 1-year experience in supervising staff, preferably within a unionized setting;

 Experience with budget forecasting and expenditure monitoring;

 Strong English language skills including written, oral and presentation skills. A second language would be considered an asset;

 Strong organizational and time management skills;

 Strong computer literacy skills, in particular, MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint);

 Social media marketing a definite asset;

 Knowledge of immigrant communities and settlement issues;

 Knowledge of Outcomes measurement;

 Knowledge of Surrey, North Delta, White Rock, and/or Langley communities an asset;

 Ability to manage multiple priorities and timelines, in a fast-paced environment;

 Excellent problem solving ability, discretion and judgement;

 Able to work independently and collegially in a team environment;

 Innovative, flexible, and able to manage change and uncertainty;

 BC Driver’s License and access to personal vehicle;

 Willing to work some evenings and weekends, as needed.


A criminal record check is required as a part of this process.



Application Requirements



To apply, please upload your resume and cover letter as separate attachments. Please note that only Word or PDF formats can be accepted. As part of the application process, you will be prompted to complete a short questionnaire. Please ensure all questions are answered.

To view all opportunities at DIVERSEcity visit www.dcrs.ca/work-with-us/.



Additional Information



This position is considered an essential service, recruitment is on-going. These are unprecedented times, and DIVERSEcity’s top priority is to ensure the safety of all our employees, clients, volunteers and candidates; recruitment for this position will be conducted virtually.


A comprehensive job description will be provided to all candidates shortlisted for interviews.


DIVERSEcity is committed to employment equity and encourages applications from people of all gender identities and expressions, persons with disabilities, Indigenous peoples and visible minorities. Persons with disabilities who anticipate needing accommodations for any part of the application and hiring process may contact our HR department at hr@dcrs.ca. Any personal information provided will be maintained in confidence.



About DIVERSEcity



DIVERSEcity Community Resources Society is a registered charity devoted to helping newcomers. For 40 years we have focused on providing specialized services newcomers to find employment, learn English, find housing, deal with family challenges, work through mental health issues and access medical care. DIVERSEcity is a client-centred organization committed to quality and accountability. We value growth, respect, integrity and compassion. To learn more about DIVERSEcity visit us at https://www.dcrs.ca/.


We thank all applicants for their interest in this opportunity; however, only those selected for an interview will be contacted.
